#. <section class="sutta" id="an10.98"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an10.98:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 10"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 10"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.98:0.2"
msgid "10. Upālivagga"
msgstr "10. With Upāli"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an10.98:0.3"
msgid "98. Therasutta"
msgstr "98. A Senior Mendicant"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an10.98:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Dasahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato thero bhikkhu yassaṃ yassaṃ disāyaṃ "
"viharati, phāsuyeva viharati."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, a senior mendicant with ten qualities lives comfortably in "
"whatever region they live."

msgctxt "an10.98:1.2"
msgid "Katamehi dasahi?"
msgstr "What ten?"

msgctxt "an10.98:1.3"
msgid "Thero hoti rattaññū cirapabbajito, "
msgstr "They are senior and have long gone forth. "

msgctxt "an10.98:1.4"
msgid "sīlavā hoti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"They’re ethical, restrained in the code of conduct, and accomplished in "
"appropriate behavior and means of collecting alms. Seeing danger in the "
"slightest fault, they keep the rules they’ve undertaken."

msgctxt "an10.98:1.5"
msgid "samādāya sikkhati sikkhāpadesu, bahussuto hoti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"They’re very learned, remembering and keeping what they’ve learned. These "
"teachings are good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the "
"end, meaningful and well-phrased, describing a spiritual practice that’s "
"entirely full and pure. They are very learned in such teachings, remembering "
"them, reinforcing them by recitation, mentally scrutinizing them, and "
"comprehending them theoretically."

msgctxt "an10.98:1.6"
msgid ""
"diṭṭhiyā suppaṭividdho, ubhayāni kho panassa pātimokkhāni vitthārena "
"svāgatāni honti suvibhattāni suppavattīni suvinicchitāni suttaso "
"anubyañjanaso, "
msgstr ""
"Both monastic codes have been passed down to them in detail, well analyzed, "
"well mastered, well judged in both the rules and accompanying material. "

msgctxt "an10.98:1.7"
msgid "adhikaraṇasamuppādavūpasamakusalo hoti, "
msgstr "They’re skilled in raising and settling disciplinary issues. "

msgctxt "an10.98:1.8"
msgid "dhammakāmo hoti piyasamudāhāro abhidhamme abhivinaye uḷārapāmojjo, "
msgstr ""
"They love the teachings and are a delight to converse with, being full of "
"joy in the teaching and training. "

msgctxt "an10.98:1.9"
msgid ""
"santuṭṭho hoti "
"itarītaracīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārena, "
msgstr ""
"They’re content with any kind of robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines "
"and supplies for the sick. "

#. VAR: abhikkantapaṭikkante → abhikkante paṭikkante (bj) | abhikkantapaṭikkanto (mr)
msgctxt "an10.98:1.10"
msgid "pāsādiko hoti abhikkantapaṭikkante susaṃvuto antaraghare nisajjāya, "
msgstr ""
"They look impressive when going out and coming back, and are well restrained "
"when sitting in an inhabited area. "

msgctxt "an10.98:1.11"
msgid ""
"catunnaṃ jhānānaṃ ābhicetasikānaṃ diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ nikāmalābhī "
"hoti akicchalābhī akasiralābhī, "
msgstr ""
"They get the four absorptions—blissful meditations in the present life that "
"belong to the higher mind—when they want, without trouble or difficulty. "

msgctxt "an10.98:1.12"
msgid ""
"āsavānañca khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ "
"abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"They realize the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this "
"very life, and they live having realized it with their own insight due to "
"the ending of defilements."

msgctxt "an10.98:1.13"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, bhikkhave, dasahi dhammehi samannāgato thero bhikkhu yassaṃ "
"yassaṃ disāyaṃ viharati, phāsuyeva viharatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"A senior mendicant with these ten qualities lives comfortably in whatever "
"region they live.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an10.98:1.14"
msgid "Aṭṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
